Neurotranscriptomics practical

Melyssa Minto

13 April, 2021

Background

This script will use the data from Engram-specific transcriptome profiling of contextual memory consolidation to find differential gene expression in Engram cells between Fear-conditioned and control experiments.

Setup for analysis

Packages that need to be installed and loaded are

  • tidyverse

  • DESeq2

  • edgeR

  • dendextend

  • reshape2

library(tidyverse)
library(DESeq2)

package GenomeInfoDb was built under R version 4.0.4package matrixStats was built under R version 4.0.4
library(edgeR)
library(reshape2)
library(dendextend)
package dendextend was built under R version 4.0.4

Loading data

Next we want to read in the data. Each samples counts are stored in a separate file. files into a count matrix

tail(counts)
# filter out the htseq stats 
counts = counts[!c(grepl("__no_feature", counts$SYMBOL)| 
                   grepl("__ambiguous", counts$SYMBOL)| 
                   grepl("__too_low_aQual", counts$SYMBOL)|  
                   grepl("__not_aligned", counts$SYMBOL)| 
                   grepl("__alignment_not_unique", counts$SYMBOL)), ]

tail(counts)

Qulaity control

# adding read depths to metadata
metadata = data.frame(GEO_Accession = accession,
           depth = colSums(counts[,2:ncol(counts)]) ) %>% 
  left_join(SraRunTable) 
Joining, by = "GEO_Accession"
